PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1783653540
OL,3,CRecord broken for most 34C days in a
OL,4,Cyear as third heatwave hits UK
OL,6,FThe hot, sunny weather is caused by
OL,7,Fhigh pressure, and Thursday and Friday
OL,8,Fwill be see peak temperatures.
OL,10,FOn Friday, Manchester could climb to
OL,11,F32C, Glasgow will see highs of 27C,
OL,12,Fand Newcastle could reach 27C on
OL,13,FThursday afternoon.
OL,15,FAreas of Northern Ireland could also
OL,16,Fsee highs of up to 28C on Friday.
OL,18,FHumidity is lower than in June, but UV
OL,19,Flevels remain high so the NHS
OL,20,Frecommend wearing sunscreen and hats.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
